task_description: Facing the building to your South-East (approx. 123°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roof.
I have now seen the top of the building, so I will look down to see its base to get a sense of the full height.

Having seen the top at +30 degrees and the base at -30 degrees, I can now estimate the height by counting the floors; I count approximately 8 floors, and assuming a standard floor height of 3 meters, the total height is about 24 meters.
